âœ… Bonus: Virtual DOM vs. Real DOM
The real DOM is what the browser actually renders. Changing it is expensive.
The Virtual DOM is Reactâ€™s in-memory representation. React uses it to figure out the minimal, most efficient set of changes before touching the real DOM.
Result? Faster, smoother UIs with less layout thrashing
